Many languages are expressions (as opposed to statements) including C-like languages. I&#x27;ve always thought that &#x27;return&#x27; itself was redundant. If a compound statement was defined to return the value of the final (executed) statement, then functional methods would get much simpler. And remove the need for the &#x27;?&#x27; operator for instance.<p>e.g.<p><pre><code>   int foo(int x) {   bar(x,y); }
</code></pre>
or<p><pre><code>   x = {if (foo() > 9) true; else false; }</code></pre>
